# Styling Convention

- Use Tailwind utility classes exclusively for all component styling.
- Never create or edit CSS class rules in .css files (styles.css is for CSS custom properties and the filter-select portal only).
- Never use BEM naming (block__element--modifier) or semantic className values that require a stylesheet.
- Every className must resolve to Tailwind utilities or reference a constant from utils/.
- Use the `cn()` utility from `utils/cn.ts` for conditional/dynamic classes.
- Reusable class compositions live in `utils/chartStyles.ts`, `utils/sharedStyles.ts`, or `utils/filtersLayout.ts` as exported string constants (CLS_* naming).
- For SVG elements inside Recharts, use inline `style` props — Tailwind cannot target SVG internals.
- For Recharts portaled components, use `wrapperStyle` prop or arbitrary variants like `[&_.recharts-class]:utility`.
- CSS custom properties are defined in `styles.css` (:root) and mapped to Tailwind via `@theme` in `index.css`.

# Available Theme Tokens

Colors: bg, surface, surface-hover, border, border-strong, text-primary, text-secondary, text-muted, accent, accent-hover, accent-light, accent-text, green, green-light, tag-bg, tag-text, sort-asc, sort-desc
Radii: radius-sm (6px), radius-md (10px), radius-lg (14px)
Shadows: shadow-sm, shadow-md
Fonts: font-sans (DM Sans), font-mono (DM Mono)

# Usage Examples

```tsx
// Correct: Tailwind utility classes
<div className={cn(CLS_CHART_PANEL, "min-h-[330px]")}>

// Correct: conditional classes
<button className={cn(CLS_CHART_SCALE_TOGGLE_BTN, isActive && CLS_CHART_SCALE_TOGGLE_BTN_ACTIVE)}>

// Wrong: BEM class requiring stylesheet
<div className="chart-panel chart-panel--pie">
```

# Dashboard & Chart Performance (do not regress)

These rules exist because of confirmed regressions (layout thrashing, bar flicker on hover, lag when picking an institute). Do not change or remove them without explicitly re-testing all dashboard bar charts with the mouse held over the chart during load and filter changes.

## Dashboard layout (`Dashboard.tsx`)

- The state-map + main-chart grid row must use **`items-stretch`** and the same cell wrapper class on both columns (`MAP_CHART_ROW_CELL_CLASS`: `flex h-full min-h-[310px] flex-col`). Both `StateMap` and `BarChartPanel` (`fillHeight`, `h-full flex-1`) must fill their cell. Do **not** set a fixed `height`/`maxHeight` on only the chart column from a JS measurement of the map — that locks the chart shorter than the row when the grid stretches.
- When filters change, refetch only **filter-aware** analytics endpoints. Do not re-call endpoints that ignore filters (e.g. `getProjectTermThemeCloud()`) on every `analyticsOptions` change — load those once on mount.
- Do not remount heavy chart panels on every filter change via a composite `key` (e.g. `activityPieFilterKey`) unless unavoidable; prefer updating `data` / `pie` props.
- While filtered data is refetching (`refreshing`), pass `suppressAnimation` (or equivalent) to bar charts so bars snap instead of re-animating on stale data.
- Defer swapping the main slot from IC chart → Top Orgs until fresh data is ready when the IC filter was **just** applied (avoid showing stale org data mid-fetch).

## Bar charts (`BarChartPanel.tsx`, `VerticalOnlyBarShape.tsx`)

- **Do not combine** `barAnimation="vertical"` (custom `VerticalOnlyBarShape` + per-bar `requestAnimationFrame` + `setState`) with mouse-driven parent re-renders. That pairing caused bars to rise/fall repeatedly on hover. Default: use Recharts built-in animation (`barAnimation` omitted or `"default"`).
- **Do not** drive bar-chart tooltips with React state updated on every `mousemove` (e.g. `useChartCursorTooltip` setting position state each frame). Tooltips must not force a full `BarChartPanel` re-render on cursor movement. Use Recharts’ anchored tooltip or update a fixed overlay via DOM refs without re-rendering the chart.
- **Do not** tie `VerticalOnlyBarShape` bar ids to Recharts’ `x` coordinate; use stable payload fields (`full_label`, `short_label`, etc.).
- `ResizeObserver` for `fillHeight`: debounce with `requestAnimationFrame`, ignore sub-pixel height deltas (< 1px), prefer `getBoundingClientRect().height` over raw `offsetHeight` if layout is in flux.
- Avoid `syncVerticalBarSnapKey` / `clearVerticalBarHeightStore` running in render in ways that reset animation during unrelated parent updates.

## Recharts tooltips & cursor

- `Tooltip` `cursor` highlight on horizontal bar charts is allowed; it must not be the only guard if custom bar shapes are used — custom shapes must tolerate Recharts relayout without restarting animation.
- `useChartCursorTooltip` is acceptable on **line** charts (`LineChartPanel.tsx`) where there are no custom per-bar RAF animations. Do not wire the same mousemove→setState pattern into `BarChartPanel` without the DOM-ref pattern above.

## Before merging dashboard/chart changes

Manually verify on `/dashboard`:

1. Projects by Institute — load chart, keep mouse moving over bars during and after animation: bars must not oscillate.
2. Click an institute bar — filter applies without prolonged jank; Top Orgs chart appears with stable bars.
3. Apply/clear filters — no full-page chart remount flicker; pie chart does not replay its 700ms intro animation on every filter tweak unless data truly requires it.
